Picture: Supplied
Thornhill SAPS are investigating a case of culpable homicide following an accident that occurred in the early hours of this morning (28/10/2017).
The driver of an Iveco and his passenger were travelling on the N2 in the direction of Knysna, when the driver, in his 30s, allegedly lost control of the vehicle and it veered off the road into the bushes.
Police said the driver was fatally injured and his passenger was taken for medical treatment.
The name of the victim will be released after his family is informed.
Police investigations continue.


